summary:
I am a Lecturer (Assistant Professor) in Economics at the University of Essex.
I graduated with a PhD from the Paris School of Economics (PSE).
My primary research interest lies in the fields of Environmental Economics and Development Economics. I am also interested in Income Inequality and International Economics. The overarching theme of my research focuses on both developing theories and applying empirical analysis to describe the economic performance of natural resource countries.
